President Biden welcomed President Herzog of Israel to the White House. They discussed the strong partnership between the US and Israel, ways to deepen cooperation, and the US commitment to Israel's security. They also talked about global and regional issues, including the threats posed by Iran. The two presidents celebrated the agreement resolving the maritime boundary dispute between Israel and Lebanon, mediated by the US. President Biden praised Israel's statecraft and courage, and highlighted the potential for a more stable and prosperous region. He also expressed support for Israel's integration into the Arab world and welcomed improved diplomatic relations with Turkey. President Biden condemned anti-Semitism and criticized the biased nature of the UN Commission of Inquiry on Israel. He emphasized the importance of deescalating the security situation in the West Bank and reiterated that a negotiated two-state solution is the best way to achieve lasting peace. They also discussed promoting coexistence and countering extremists.